solution: ```class Solution {
    public int reverse(int x) {
        int rev = 0;
        while (x != 0) {
            int pop = x % 10;
            x /= 10;
            if (rev > Integer.MAX_VALUE / 10 || (rev == Integer.MAX_VALUE / 10 && pop > 7)) return 0;
            if (rev < Integer.MIN_VALUE / 10 || (rev == Integer.MIN_VALUE / 10 && pop < -8)) return 0;
            rev = rev * 10 + pop;
        }
        return rev;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log10|x|)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iteratively pop the last digit and push it onto the reversed number while checking for 32-bit overflow before each multiplication/addition. This avoids any 64-bit storage and handles negatives naturally.

